dialog.TEXT: War. War never changes. When atomic fire consumed the earth, those who survived did so in great underground vaults. When they opened, their inhabitants moved through the ruins of the old world to build new societies, establish new villages, form new tribes. As the decades passed, what had been the American Southwest united under the banner of the New Republic of California, dedicated to the old-world values of democracy and the rule of law.

Guerra. La guerra nunca cambia. Cuando el fuego atmico consumi la tierra, aquellos que sobrevivieron lo hicieron en grandes bvedas subterrneas. Cuando se abrieron, sus habitantes se trasladaron a travs de las ruinas del viejo mundo para construir nuevas sociedades, establecer nuevas aldeas, formar tribus. A medida que pasaban las dcadas, lo que haba sido el suroeste de Estados Unidos se uni bajo la bandera de la Nueva Repblica de California, dedicada a los valores del viejo mundo de la democracia y el estado de derecho.

War. War never changes. When atomic fire consumed the earth, those who survived did so in great underground vaults. When they opened, their inhabitants moved through the ruins of the old world to build new societies, establish new villages, form new tribes. As the decades passed, what had been the American Southwest united under the banner of the New Republic of California, dedicated to the old-world values of democracy and the rule of law.
